  "text": "Analytically, we show that almost any 5 assignment of fixed XY angle measurements on a n = 2 γ -row, 2-column cluster state (where γ is an integer) gives a random unitary set U B which is universal in U (2 n ). We use a Lie algebraic approach outlined by [CITATION_1] , and observations in [18, 19] to prove this result. In particular, when γ = 1 we get that almost any assignment of fixed XY angle measurements generates universal sets U B ⊂ U (4), which in general can be invertible, partially invertible or non invertible.",
